        break;
      case 1:
        context.goNamed(Routes.personalInformation.name);
        break;
      case 2:
        context.goNamed(Routes.paymentMethods.name);
        break;
    }
  },
),
\
So here’s how it works: when a side menu item gets tapped, we navigate to a specific tab by passing the target route name. I have separated  from  because they fulfill different purposes—one is for , and the other is for routing—even though I have used almost similar keys.As you can see, we have not used any string comparison. If you mistype a string, the connection is broken, so be careful not to use strings. Instead, use compiler features to catch errors during compile time rather than at runtime.But how does the home page change pages? 🤔One of the common layout widgets in Flutter is IndexedStack, which shows a single child from a list of children. So by selecting an item, we rebuild the home page with the selected tab, and it shows the selected page, which uses internally.Update your  with the following:import 'package:appleid_dashboard/router/routes.dart';
